<HEADLINE> Public Security Organ Urged to Keep On "Strike Hard" (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Speaking of the task facing public security forces next year,
Tao called on public security organs across the country to
implement the "Public Security Working Agenda During the Ninth
Five-Year Plan (1996-2000)", in line with the arrangements worked
out in the Central Economic Working Conference and the National
Politics and Laws Working Conference.
</P>
<P>
Viewing maintenance of social stability as their highest
priority, public security organs should deepen the reforms,
improve law enforcement, strengthen basic work at grassroots
level, continue to prevent and crack down severely on various
kinds of major crimes, including economic ones.
</P>
<P>
Close attention should be paid to improvement of professional
ethics of police, he said, adding that police forces should help
ensure China's smooth resumption of exercising the sovereignty
over Hong Kong and the successful opening of the 15th National
Congress of the Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should be redoubled to adhere to the principle of
"strike hard," including strict prevention and control, Tao said.
</P>
<P>
An instant-reaction system should be established to speed up
the efficiency of the police, local police stations should be
reinforced, and the quality of the police should be improved, Tao
told the conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
