<HEADLINE> Tianjin Enterprises Receive International Quality Certificates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen enterprises in north
China's Tianjin port have received quality certificates issued by
the International Standard Organization, Yu Rumin, deputy director
of the Tianjin Port Office, said today.
</P>
<P>
"The port is getting enough qualified enterprises to make
itself accessible to international markets," Yu said.
</P>
<P>
Management and quality standards issued by ISO have been
introduced into the port since October, 1989. So far 13 files have
been compiled, and one quality management brochure produced to
support the standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
