<HEADLINE> Procurators' Conference In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- A five-day National
Procurators' Conference for examining this year's work and making
plans for the new year opened in the Chinese capital today.
</P>
<P>
The procurators will also discuss enforcement of amendments to
the Criminal Procedural Law and the Criminal Law.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Siqing, procurator-general of the Supreme People's
Procuratorate(SPP), sponsored the conference, in which Liang
Guoqing, deputy chief procurator of the SPP, delivered a work
report.
</P>
<P>
Liang said that China's procurators have focused attention on
major corruption cases involving government officials since the
beginning of the year, and have given a strong push to the
country's anti-corruption drive.
</P>
<P>
He said that procurators nationwide have participated in the
national anti-crime campaign, which started April 28, and have
contributed to halting the rising crime rate.
</P>
<P>
Liang listed three major tasks for procurators in
1997: continuing the investigation and prosecution of major
corruption cases involving government officials; hitting major
criminal activities hard; and carrying out their supervisory work
in a strict fashion.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that procurators across the country should make
every effort to improve their law-enforcement ability, to help
promote the country's economic development and see to the smooth
implementation of China's reform and opening-up drive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
