<HEADLINE> Canadian PM to Visit Thailand Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien is expected to lead a 500-strong delegation to Thailand
next month to promote bilateral ties and seek closer bilateral
economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian delegation, which is expected to include premiers
of all Canadian provinces and some 250 leading Canadian
businessmen, will be the largest such party of foreign dignitaries
ever to visit Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Chretien is scheduled to lead the Canadian delegation to
Thailand on January 16-20 to sign a number of bilateral documents,
including pacts on environmental protection, education and
agricultural cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He will visit South Korea and the Philippines before he arrives
in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers said that Thai Prime Minister Chavalit
Yongchaiyudh and Canadian Ambassador Manfred von Nostitz met
Monday to discuss the arrangements for Chretien's upcoming visit.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
