<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Privatization Brings 2.9 Billion Dollars to Portugal's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The Portuguese government has
sped up its privatization process this year to add about 2.9
billion U.S. dollars, or three percent of the GDP, to the state
treasury.
</P>
<P>
The privatization process in Portugal for 1996 and 1997 is
intended to promote the productivity and competitiveness of
state-owned industries, cut down public financial deficiency and
pave the way for its European monetary System membership.
</P>
<P>
The privatization process so far this year has covered the
telecommunications sector, the BFE bank and a cement company. The
government plans to privatize the tobacco sector by the end of
this year.
</P>
<P>
Next year, the privatization program is expected to produce
some 2.7 billion dollars for the state treasury. 
</P>
</TEXT>
