<HEADLINE> Becker Not to Play Davis Cup Tie Against Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Boris Becker will not play for
Germany in its first-round Davis Cup tie against Spain in
February, his manager Axel Meyer-Woelden said in Munich on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Meyer-Woelden said Becker's withdrawal was "related to his
health" and to the fact that the February 7-9 match will be played
on clay, Becker's least favorite surface.
</P>
<P>
Becker has said that his main ambition for 1997 is to regain
the No. 1 ranking, now held by American Pete Sampras. 
</P>
