<HEADLINE> Bomb Hits Higuita's Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Unidentified attackers bombed
the home of Colombian goalkeeper Rene Higuita, causing property
damage but no injuries, according to local reports.
</P>
<P>
Higuita, a flamboyant figure in Colombia's soccer team in the
1994 World Cup finals, was out when the bomb exploded at his house
in the northwest city of Medellin on Sunday evening.
</P>
<P>
Bombers forced their way past the maid into the house and
detonated a charge of dynamite, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Higuita has declined to join the national squad for qualifying
matches for the 1998 World Cup, saying he needed a break. 
</P>
</TEXT>
