<HEADLINE> China's Largest Automobile Sealing Strips Production Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- A 36-million US dollar
technology-upgrading project has helped build a Sino-Italian joint
sealing company in Shanghai into China's largest base for the
production of sealing strips for automobiles.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Saic-Saiag Sealing Company, which was jointly set
up in 1995 by the Shanghai Automotive Company, Shanghai Yongying
Corporation and Italy's Saiag Industrial S.P.A., used the spending
to introduce hi-tech and equipment from Italy and Britain to
improve its production.
</P>
<P>
It imported a complete set of equipment of mixing, extrusion
and finishing, as well as Saiag's technologies, which reach
international standards, to produce high-quality sealing products,
including solid rubber sealing strips with flocking and
joint-corners, as well as multi-component sealing strips.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture has formed an annual production capacity of
300,000 sets of sealing strips for "Santana" sedans, as well as
30,000 sets of sealing products for export.
</P>
<P>
The technological-upgrading project is expected to help the
company increase sales by 430 million yuan and 100 million yuan in
profits per year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
