<HEADLINE> Chile's Trade Deficit Nears One Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Chile's trade deficit
reached 980 million U.S. dollars by November 30, with 14.11
billion dollars in exports and 15.09 billion dollars in imports,
according the central bank today.
</P>
<P>
In November alone, Chile suffered a deficit of 248 million
dollars with 1.176 billion dollars of exports versus 1.424 billion
of imports.
</P>
<P>
The bank attributed the situation to the price drops in Chile's
main exports: copper and pulp by 13.6 percent during the first 11
months of the year compared with the same period last year and its
increase in imports, mainly petroleum, by 10.1 percent. 
</P>
