<HEADLINE> Yunnan Strives to Wipe Out Poverty by 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan
Province has pledged to help all people living under the poverty
line to lead a better life before the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
The pledge was announced at a provincial anti-poverty
conference in the province's capital city of Kunming.
</P>
<P>
The province has an impoverished population of five million
living in 73 mountainous counties or areas inhabited by ethnic
groups.
</P>
<P>
Participants at the meeting agreed that the policy of helping
the poor to get rich through developing production will continue
to be implemented in the coming years.
</P>
<P>
Poor areas should place the emphasis on grain production. Mass
campaigns will be launched to improve soil, build water
conservancy projects, roads and power plants, and popularize
modern agro-techniques.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government will allocate 450 million yuan in
special funds to help the poor annually. Each poverty-stricken
township will receive 500,000 yuan as assistance for economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Leading party and government officials at various levels are
required to have regular contacts with designated poor
areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
