<HEADLINE> First Train For Guangzhou Subway Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The first new subway train
for Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong province, has
rolled off the production line in Germany.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities say that the Adtranz company in Berlin,
Germany, has finished building the first train for the city's
subway, the construction of which is now under way.
</P>
<P>
According to a contract signed three years ago, the German
company will produce 20 subway trains for Guangzhou. Each train
will have six compartments and a length of 140 meters, with a
seating capacity of 1,592 passengers.
</P>
<P>
Orange colored, and with red stripes, the train will be
equipped with a station reporting system making announcements in
Mandarin, Cantonese, and English. It also has an alarm system.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities said that all the trains are expected to be
completed next April, prior to delivery to Guangzhou. 
