<HEADLINE> Advanced System to Monitor Sand Content in Rivers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 24 (Xinhua) -- China has worked out a
telemetering system of a world advanced level for round-the-clock
monitoring of the content of sand in rivers.
</P>
<P>
The system will help deal with sands that grind the generating
units of hydro-electrical power stations, and regulate sand
silting in reservoirs.
</P>
<P>
The computer-controled system, invented by the Sanmenxia Water
Control Administration, will provide accurate data for technicians
to decide the best time for power generation in the sandy Yellow
River. 
