<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oil, Gas Gushing from Deep Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- China has acquired high-yield
oil and gas from the country's deepest onshore horizontal well,
officials at the Shixi Oilfield have reported.
</P>
<P>
Shixi workers recently pumped a stream from the well with daily
output of 1,025 tons of crude oil and 272,000 cubic meters of gas.
</P>
<P>
The desert well is in the heart of the Junggar Basin in
northwest China. The horizontal well, almost 5,000 meters in
depth, is the deepest of its kind in the country.
</P>
<P>
Drilling of the well started in May, and was completed on
October 30 this year. During the period, workers have broken a
number of drilling records.
</P>
<P>
Development of horizontal wells involve new and efficient
technology. Sinking of the well has helped China win experience in
developing special oil and gas bearing structures in the desert of
the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
