<HEADLINE> Guatemala Investigates Properties of Former President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The Guatemalan government
is investigating properties of former President Jorge Serrano who
has been living in asylum in Panama for three years, Guatemalan
Ambassador to Panama Gisela Godinez Sazo said today.
</P>
<P>
The investigation will cover Panama and other countries where
Jorge Serrano could have investments so as to determine whether
his money came from Guatemala's public treasury, according to the
ambassador.
</P>
<P>
Jorge Serrano ruled Guatemala from 1991 to 1993, and fled to
Panama on June 1, 1993, after the failure of his May 25 "self-coup
d'etat" designed to dissolve the parliament and the courts of
justice.
</P>
<P>
He has several horses in Panama and is the owner of a luxurious
Country Club for the wealthiest.
</P>
<P>
Last week, one of his horses won a race of the Caribbean
International Classic in Puerto Rico, which alone brought him a
80,000-dollar income. 
</P>
</TEXT>
