<HEADLINE> Maldini, Weah Sidelined for One Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The two key players George Weah
and Paolo Maldini of AC Milan will be sidelined for at least one
month following injuries suffered in Sunday's league match against
Parma, according to reports from Milan.
</P>
<P>
Both players had to leave the field during the home match at
which added injury to the insult of a 1-0 defeat which dropped AC
Milan to seventh place in the overall league standings.
</P>
<P>
Weah from Liberia will be sidelined between 30 to 45 days
following an ankle sprain, club officials said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Maldini, the captain of Italy's national team, had a cheek bone
fracture fixed by doctors on Monday, the club noted. He won't be
back to action before one month. 
</P>
