<HEADLINE> China Speeds Up Construction of Unmanned Power Substations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 24 (Xinhua)-- More than 210 unmanned
power substations have been brought into use in China since 1994,
serving to upgrade power grids in the country's rural areas.
</P>
<P>
China began nationwide construction of substations after all
the six substations in Sanhe City of Hebei Province succeeded in
unmanned operations in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Power Industry has now encouraged other
provinces to follow the example. Provisional statistics show that
263 unmanned substations have been built in the countryside.
</P>
<P>
The power substations, equipped with remote sensing and
automation facilities, save labor and material resources, and also
improve management and operational quality.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has set guidelines for substation construction. It
says that power substations to be built should all be capable of
being unmanned, and that remote sensing and other facilities
should be installed in existing substations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
