<HEADLINE> China to Open First Tea Factory to Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 24 (Xinhua)-- The Huangshan Mountain Tunxi Tea
Factory in Anhui Province has been authorized by the Ministry of
Foreign Economic Relations and Trade to conduct import and export
businesses.
</P>
<P>
It is the first tea factory in China to have this right, and
has also been declared open to overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
China is famous for its tea, and the Huangshan Mountain is one
of China's major tea growing areas. But the Huangshan factory
suffered deficits because it had to buy raw materials at a high
price, while selling its products to specialized import and export
companies at a lower price.
</P>
<P>
The factory is now encouraged to produce more green, black,
scented and other tea products, and promote the area's tea
economy. 
</P>
