<HEADLINE> Extremely Light-weighted Infants Survive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nanjing, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Premature twin girl babies
with extremely low weights, who were born more than a month ago,
have survived and are growing well.
</P>
<P>
The two babies, weighing 1,500 grams and 1,250 grams, were born
at only 31 weeks gestation.
</P>
<P>
The Suzhou city women and children health care hospital carried
out a Ceasarean section on the new mother when medical workers
found that she was suffering from early birth complications.
</P>
<P>
Medical test also found that one fetus was suffering from
oxygen starvation and fetal movement became slow.
</P>
<P>
Medical workers used special techniques to help the lungs of
the babies.
</P>
<P>
Now the weights of the two babies has increased to 1,750 grams
and 1,550 grams.  
</P>
</TEXT>
