<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Indian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Hindustan Times
</P>
<P>
-- The Supreme Court Monday ordered the eviction within six
months of about 2,000 central government employees who were
allotted out-of-turn government accommodation in Delhi on special
compassionate grounds.
</P>
<P>
The Times of India
</P>
<P>
-- Efforts to evolve a consensus in favor of All-India Congress
Committee (AICC) President Sitaram Kesri as new chief of Congress
parliamentary party (CPP) were intensified further Monday.
