<HEADLINE> Hubei Flood Victims Have Enough Food and Fine Shelter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 24 (Xinhua) -- More than 20 million flood
victims in central China's Hubei Province will have enough food
and housing against the cold this winter.
</P>
<P>
Since June, floods caused by 10 heavy downpours have destroyed
more than two billion kilograms of grain, demolished 700,000
residential buildings and damaged another 1.3 million homes in the
province.
</P>
<P>
Following the floods the province has appealed for donations,
reduced taxes on farmers, organized flood victims to rebuild their
homeland, and transported grain from areas enjoying good
agricultural harvests to flood-hit areas.
</P>
<P>
So far the province has repaired all damaged houses, handed out
115 million kilograms of food, and allocated 113 million yuan
(about 13.6 million US dollars) of relief funding to flood victims
to help them get through the winter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
