<HEADLINE> hke- Romania Warns Against Election in Separatist Region of Moldova </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Romania said on Monday that
the "presidential election" on Sunday in a breakaway region of
neighboring Moldova would only increase the tensions there.
</P>
<P>
A foreign ministry statement reiterated Romania's continued
support for the stance held by the Moldovan government against the
election in the region east of the river Dnestr.
</P>
<P>
The election in the region, known as Transdnestr, would make
the negotiations between the Moldovan government and the regional
authorities more difficult, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Dominated by ethnic Russians and Ukrainians, Transdnestr
declared independence in 1991 from Moldova, a tiny former Soviet
republic sandwiched in between Romania and Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
The Moldovan authorities have promised "widest possible"
autonomy to Transdnestr under the precondition of a united Moldova.
</P>
<P>
Peru Lucinschi, who was elected Moldovan president in run-off
elections on December 1, said on Monday that the election in the
Transdnestr was only "local election within Moldova."
</P>
<P>
The Moldovan government has been negotiating with the
Transdnestr authorities for years but have failed to reach an
agreement on the region's status. 
</P>
