<HEADLINE> Chinese Counties Cooperate with Colleges To Develop Local Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Some Chinese research institutes
and 13 universities and colleges have signed a contract with 14
counties in central China's Hubei Province, in a move to help the
local economy.
</P>
<P>
One official said that the large agricultural province only has
442 technicians for every 10,000 people, putting it eleventh in
China. To cope with this situation, the province has sent 290
skilled technicians, selected from colleges, research institutes,
and large state-owned enterprises, to work as deputy heads in
70-some counties or cities across the province since 1988.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that the move is intended to compensate for
the shortage of technical personnel at the grass-roots level and
to help train local technicians.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 61 colleges and 258 research institutes,
with a total staff of 1.13 million, which is promising for
developing the province's economy, he added.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, Zhongxiang City has earned some 500
million yuan in profits in recent years, thanks to the
introduction of 31 projects from the province's colleges and
research institutes.  
</P>
