<HEADLINE> Ukraine to Seek More Military Cooperation With Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine will expand military
cooperation with its strategic partner, Russia, a defense ministry
official said today.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine intended to further its military cooperation with
Russia and that the two countries have not had much joint action
in the military field, said the official at a news briefing at the
Defense Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Referring to Ukraine's present military contacts with foreign
countries and its plan next year, he said the armed forces have
developed ties with 31 countries, signing altogether 127
agreements and documents on military cooperation, of which 46 were
signed this year.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine will sign military cooperation agreements with nine
other countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
On cooperation with NATO, the official was quoted as saying
that Ukraine seeks military cooperation with NATO on the basis of
the principle of mutual benefit and partnership.
</P>
<P>
He said that his country has taken an active part in the bloc's
"Peace for Partnership" program.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, Ukraine participated in 98 activities of the program,
and will take part in more than 230 other military activities
under the 1996-1998 PFP program.
</P>
<P>
Among these activities, the most important will be a
Ukraine-based joint military war games involving the United
States, Italy, Turkey and Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the four countries held their first
coordination conference today in the west Ukrainian city of Lvov,
where the military exercise, code-named Cooperative Neighbor-97,
will be held next summer, local press reported.
</P>
<P>
The maneuver, regarded by Ukrainian officials as an important
step to deepen international military cooperation, was meant for
the allied forces to provide refugees with assistance, transport
humanitarian aid, supervise relief distribution and protect
important buildings, participants of the coordination conference
said.
</P>
<P>
The size of the military maneuver has not been revealed.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine has taken part in the NATO-led peacekeeping forces in
Bosnia by sending 500 troops there. But the number will be reduced
to 400 in 1997.
</P>
<P>
It staged a military exercise with Germany in March and another
war game in June with 10 western countries, including the United
states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
