<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Defense Department
announced today that supreme commander Gen. George A. Joulwan of
the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) will retire next
spring.
</P>
<P>
"The United States and Europe are both more secure for his
leadership," Defense Secretary William Perry said.
</P>
<P>
