<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 23 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks were mostly
lower today amid light trading, but the Dow Jones industrial
average managed a slight gain at the late session.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip indicator advanced 4.62 points to 6,489.02,
recovering from a 31-point dip. Dow gained 180 points last week,
including a 126-point jump Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by nearly a 5-to-4
margin on the New York Stock Exchange, with the NYSE volume
totaling 339.94 million shares, much fewer than 650.09 million in
the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock index fell 1.94 to 746.93, and
the NYSE's composite index fell 0.82 to 393.29.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index fell 9.08 to 1,279.48, and the
American Stock Exchange's market value index fell 1.03 to 580.98.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq market showed the worst damage as technology shares
gave up some ground for the second consecutive session.
</P>
<P>
Stocks drew some early support from the bond market, where
prices improved and the yield on the 30-year Treasury bond fell to
6.58 percent, down from late Friday's 6.60 percent.
</P>
<P>
There was little market reaction to a report showing that
personal incomes rebounded in November and consumer spending
showed surprising strength at the start of the Christmas sales
season. 
