<HEADLINE> China to Strengthen Checks on Operation of State-owned Assets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- China is yto strengthen checks
on the operation of state-owned assets, according to a national
conference held in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Youcai, director of the State Administration of State
Property, told the conference that in 1997, the maintenance and
increase of state-owned assets will be a major standard for the
government to judge the achievements of operators.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, also vice-minister of finance, said that it is necessary
to study links between workers' salaries, economic returns of
enterprises, and the maintenance and increase of the state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the scope of checks on increment of state-owned
assets should be exercised on all enterprises owned by governments
at provincial and prefecture level, and 80 percent of enterprises
owned by governments at county level.
</P>
<P>
The official also suggested sending more boards of supervisors
to enterprises, setting up modern enterprise systems in more
enterprises, and conducting experimental tests on the improvement
of capital structures.
</P>
<P>
Zhang also urged government officials to strengthen the
management of property registration and to improve handling of
disputes over property.  
</P>
</TEXT>
