<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Closer Vietnamese-Chinese Cooperation in Science Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Deputy Prime Minister
Nguyen Khanh today called for stronger cooperation between
Vietnamese and Chinese scientists.
</P>
<P>
Khanh made the call while meeting with the delegation of the
Chinese Scientific and Technical Association (CSTA) led by CSTA
chairman, Zhou Guangzhao, who is also head of the Chinese Academy
of Science.
</P>
<P>
Khanh briefed his guests on Vietnam's policy on scientific and
technological development and on application of scientific
advances into production in the process of industrialization and
modernization.
</P>
<P>
He hoped Vietnam Union of Scientific and Technical Associations
and the CSTA would enhance cooperation, thus helping promote the
friendly and cooperative ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Zhou told the Vietnamese leader about the outcome of his
delegation's working sessions with Vietnamese institutions and
agencies. He also spoke highly of Vietnam's achievements in
socio-economic development as well as in science and technology in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
He informed khanh of China's policy on scientific and technical
investment and development as well as its policy to promote the
training of Chinese scientists and researchers in the years to
come. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
