<HEADLINE> EC to Host Donor Info Meeting for Former Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC)
has said it would, together with the World Bank, co-host a Donor
Information Meeting here on January 9-10 to help donors prepare
for the next pledging conference for the former Yugoslavia
scheduled for early in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The Commission said that implementation of the 1996
reconstruction program in the former Yugoslavia was "progressing
well" and had accelerated in recent months.
</P>
<P>
It noted that about 1,200 million U.S. dollars of the 1996
donor pledges was currently under implementation, of which 720
million dollars had actually been disbursed to implementing
organizations.
</P>
<P>
"With a significant amount of 1996 pledges expected to be under
implementation or disbursed by year end, fresh money will be
needed in time to prevent implementation delays," the Commission
said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
According to the Commission, the Information Meeting will be
used to review the achievements and status of the 1996 program and
to discuss the sectoral priorities, objectives and financial needs
of the 1997 program.
</P>
<P>
The target for the full four-year (1996-1999) construction
program for the former Yugoslavia is 5.1 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
