<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Report: Factory Explosion Kills Several Near Houston </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 23 (Xinhua) -- A metal-fabricating factory
near southern U.S. city Houston exploded late Sunday, killing at
least five people, local media reports said.
</P>
<P>
Fire officials said that the blast happened at the Wyman Gordon
Forging Co., a defense contractor in northwestern Harris County,
Texas.
</P>
<P>
Body parts were thrown as far as 100 yards outside the
building, Fire Department officials said.
</P>
<P>
Local TV reported five people were dead, two others injured and
two to three were missing.
</P>
<P>
The blast occurred near a 30,000-ton press in the plant, which
produces extruded pipe used in power and chemical plants.
</P>
<P>
In addition to pipe made at the Houston plant, Wyman Gordon,
which employs 1,200 people, produces high-strength forged and cast
metal parts for a wide variety of applications.
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately known what caused the explosion and how
many people were working in the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
