<DOCNO> XIE19961224.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Appeals for 91.9 Million U.S. Dollars for Liberia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations today
appealed for 91.9 million U.S. dollars for two linked initiatives
addressing urgent emergency and recovery activities for Liberia.
</P>
<P>
The UN joint inter-agency appeal for Liberia for the first half
of 1997 is coordinated by the Department of Humanitarian Affairs
(DHA) based in Geneva. According to DHA, this is the first part of
a common strategy to address the needs stemming from seven years
of civil war in Liberia. 31.2 million dollars is required to
continue relief activities for civilians and to meet the initial
basic needs of ex-combatants, internally displaced persons and
refugees during the initial reintegration phase. It will provide
initial basic food, health, water and sanitation, shelter and
infrastructure assistance. In addition, it seeks to address the
immediate needs of former child soldiers and abandoned children.
</P>
<P>
Another program coordinated by the United Nations Development
Program (UNDP) seeks 60.7 million dollars for immediate
rehabilitation and peace building activities during the whole year
of 1997. The program will focus on community reintegration and
social and economic recovery, as well as job creation,
strengthening law enforcement institutions and other elements of
civil administration, and assisting in the management of
elections.
</P>
<P>
The international community is called upon to respond
generously to these initiatives, to support the people of Liberia
in their aspirations for a new life free of war and destruction.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
