<HEADLINE> Car Bomb Explosion Kills One in Central Algiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 23 (Xinhua) -- A powerful car bomb explosion
killed one and wounded 20 in central Algiers at 1145 GMT near one
of the principal coffee-shops on a main street of the city, the
Agence France Presse (AFP) quoted Algerian officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
The attack took place after a series of clashes took place
between Algerian security forces and the Islamic extremists over
the past few days, in which 28 people were killed.
</P>
<P>
AFP said the bomb attack greatly jostled the center of Algiers,
where thousands of company employees, passers-by and pedlars are
gathering every day at the lunch-hour.
</P>
<P>
Soldiers and police, along with ambulances and staff of civil
protection organizations, were immediately dispatched to the scene
of the explosion on Rue d'Isly, near which the headquarters of the
private newspaper Liberte and the city hall are located, said AFP.
</P>
<P>
A witness said that the car was driven by a young man, who got
out of the vehicle and ran away before it blew up.
</P>
<P>
Last summer, the Islamic extremists launched a series of bomb
attacks on coffee-shops and restaurants in Algiers and other
cities, killing about 15 people and wounding a dozen others.
</P>
<P>
A high school girl was killed and another wounded in a bomb
explosion which took place last Saturday near a high school in
Douaouda, 30 kilometers west of Algiers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
