<HEADLINE> 36 UNITA Officers Ranked in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Military ranks were today
conferred on another group of 36 officers of the former rebel
UNITA movement by Angola's unified government forces in a show of
national reconciliation in the post-war era.
</P>
<P>
They include eight colonels, 10 lieutenant colonels and 18
majors who were former officers of the National Union for the
Total Independence of the Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
Earlier, nine generals were ranked, taking key military
positions from deputy chief of the general staff to the chief of
the capital military command.
</P>
<P>
All the ranked officers are expected to formally join the
government troops on January 6.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Angola Verification Mission (UNAVEM)
announced that the government of national reconciliation would
assume its function on January 25 after nearly 20 years of civil
war in the southern African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
