<HEADLINE> Air France to Open Flight Between Cuba, French Antilles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The French national carrier, Air
France, will open on January 8, 1997 a weekly air flight between
the Cuban capital of Havana and the French overseas territory of
Antilles in the Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
The passenger planes of Air France will start from Cayenne,
capital of French Guiana, and make stops at Fort-de-France and
Pointe-a-Pitre of the French Antilles, before arriving in Havana,
the Agence France Presse (AFP) quoted Air France officials as
saying today in the Cuban capital.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban national airliner, Cubana de Aviacion, has already
opened a weekly air flight between Havana and the French Antilles.
</P>
<P>
The French air company Air Outremer and Cubana de Aviacion have
each of them three flights between Cuba and mainland France each
week, having transported 48,000 passengers altogether in the first
10 months this year, against 34,000 for the whole year of 1995.
</P>
<P>
There is no shipping line between Cuba and France and the
French Antilles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
