<HEADLINE> Clinton Calls for Release of All Hostages in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 23 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
today welcomed the release of all the seven Americans and other
hostages by rebels in Peru, but called for immediate release of
all the rest of the hostages.
</P>
<P>
"The United States expresses its great appreciation to the
government of President Fujimori for the support and consideration
given to the Americans who were held, to their families, and to
the entire American community in Peru," White House press
secretary Mike McCurry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The seven Americans were among 225 captives freed Sunday night.
Clinton urged the rebels to free the remaining 140 hostages, most
of whom are Peruvian officials and Japanese businessmen.
</P>
<P>
"The United States will continue its close consultations with
Peru, Japan and all concerned governments on this situation,"
McCurry said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
