<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Declares Ukranian Diplomat Persona Non Grata </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- A Ukrainian diplomat was
declared persona non grata today and told to leave Canada by
midnight December 25.
</P>
<P>
Olexander Yushko, a vice-consul, claimed diplomatic immunity
after being accused of trying to lure young girls into his car,
the local media reported.
</P>
<P>
He was arrested on October 26 and charged with two counts of
drunk driving, possession of stolen license plates and attempting
to bribe an officer.
</P>
<P>
Since his arrest, there have been allegations in court that he
tried to entice two girls -- aged 12 and 14 -- into his car while
holding a handkerchief soaked with anesthetic.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian government made the declaration forcing Yushko to
leave after it became clear that the Ukrainian government would
not consider waiving his diplomatic immunity, the report said.
</P>
<P>
"Charges against Mr. Yushko have been held in abeyance," a
Foreign Affairs spokesman was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
"Should he ever return to Canada, he will be subject to
prosecution on those charges," the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
