<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Women Prone to Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- One in every three German women
have fallen victims to violence for at least once in their life
time, said a latest survey report.
</P>
<P>
The report, released recently by Allenbach Institute, a public
opinion survey organization, indicated that even the family
doesn't shelter women from violence in the country.
</P>
<P>
As married women are more likely to become targets of domestic
violence, it said, about 2.5 million German women are forced to
have sex with their husbands.
</P>
<P>
In addition, more than 12.5 percent of homicide cases in the
country take place between spouses, with women accounting for 67
percent of the total number of victims.
</P>
<P>
The report also said that at least 250,000 underaged girls are
sexually assaulted each year. But law enforcement authorities
could only handle 100,000 of such cases.
</P>
<P>
However, the pollster noted, the numbers revealed by survey
results are only "a tip of the iceberg" as many women victims are
reluctant to tell their stories. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
