<HEADLINE> Malaysia Airlines to Cease services into Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Airlines
announced here today that it will cease operations into Mexico
with effect from January 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The Airlines said in a statement that the cessation of its
services into Mexico is a result of the imposition of new terms by
the Mexican Civil Aviation Authorities on it.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia Airlines presently operates twice weekly on a Kuala
Lumpur - Taipei - Los Angeles - Mexico vice versa routing.
</P>
<P>
The Airlines said its services will consequently terminate at
Los Angeles and will only operate Kuala Lumpur - Taipei - Los
Angeles vice versa routing from January 1 next year.
</P>
<P>
The Airlines said it has already made arrangements to transfer
its Mexico destined and originating passenger bookings to other
airlines operating on the Los Angeles - Mexico vice versa sector.
 
</P>
