<HEADLINE> Shanghai Carrying Out Construction Supervision System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- A construction unit carrying
out a major contract in Shanghai has been found to overcharge its
client by four million yuan (480,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The overcharge came to light when the Shanghai Shenhai
Construction Supervision Company was in the process of settling
the accounts for the project in the city's Fuxin Road. A
supervision report made by the company made the unit correct their
mistake.
</P>
<P>
With the development of the municipal infrastructure, the
system of supervision and management for construction in Shanghai,
China's largest industrial and financial center, has been fully
carried out.
</P>
<P>
The system focuses on the progress rate, cost, and quality
monitoring of projects. Since the system went into practice in
1988, the supervision industry in Shanghai has covered the fields
of petrochemistry, power, port, aviation, television and
residential development.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Shanghai has 300 supervision
organizations, with 7,000 employees. These organizations have
supervised 1,700 projects worth 170 billion yuan (20.5 billion US
dollars), with the overall construction coverage of 40 million
square meters.
</P>
<P>
Hu Renwei, general manager of Shenhai has disclosed that, in
the next five years or so, construction will become a pillar
industry in the city, and the supervision system will have a
brighter future.
</P>
<P>
To meet the need of the supervision market, China is regulating
a "Construction Law". Shanghai Municipal Government has already
issued the "Regulation on the Supervision over the Construction
Projects".
</P>
<P>
In addition, Shanghai has held over 50 training classes for
supervision personnel, and over 7,500 people have received
certificates issued by the Ministry of Construction and the
Municipal Construction Committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
