<HEADLINE> Vietnam, Thailand to Promote Financial Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and Thailand have
decided to promote financial cooperation through the
Vietnam-Thailand Joint Finance Commission (VTJFC), local media
reported today.
</P>
<P>
During the first two-day meeting of the VTJFC held last Friday
in Hanoi, the two countries signed a memorandum of understanding
concerning financial and monetary policies on macro-economy, the
investment market, cooperation in tariffs, customs, banking and
infrastructure development, according to the report,
</P>
<P>
The two countries also discussed the ASEAN Free Trade area and
the ASEAN Finance Ministerial Meeting to be held early next year
in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Thailand also pledged to help Vietnam in personnel training.
</P>
<P>
The VTJFC, which was set up in December 1995, is the first
joint commission of its kind between Vietnam and other ASEAN
member countries. 
