<HEADLINE> China Establishes First Multi-Media Classroom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- China's first multi-media
classroom has been established in Beijing. It connects the Chinese
capital with other parts of the country and the world to realize
the sharing of educational resources.
</P>
<P>
The classroom uses computers and multi-media technologies to
provide remote teaching. It overcomes space limitations by
interactive technologies, two-way communications, and audio and
video teaching material.
</P>
