<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0730 GMT December 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- NATO's Supreme Allied Commander in Europe, American
General George Joulwan, said on Monday he would retire from the
position in the spring of 1997, according to a news release from
NATO's Supreme Headquarters Allied Powers Europe, which is based
in Mons, Belgium.
</P>
<P>
KIEV -- Ukraine will expand military cooperation with its
strategic partner, Russia, a defense ministry official said on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- France and Russia will launch their sixth joint space
flight in the second quarter of 1997, in which French astronaut
Leopold Eyharts will stay 21 days at the Russian space orbiter
Mir, said French Ministry of Post, Telecommunications and Space on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton Monday welcomed the
release of all the seven Americans taken hostages by rebels in
Peru, but called for immediate release of all the rest of the
hostages. 
</P>
