<HEADLINE> East Chinese Police Units and Individuals Awarded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-three police units and
600 individuals in China's Fujian Province were given awards
recently for their excellent participation in a nationwide
anti-crime campaign that started last April 28.
</P>
<P>
A senior official with the provincial public security
department said that the rising tide of criminal activities in the
province have been halted, thanks to the national anti-crime
campaign.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, the total number of crimes reported
during the May-September period was down 21.86 percent from the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The official said recent reports by related departments show
that the province's citizens generally believe that social order
and people's consciousness of safety measures have improved.
</P>
<P>
He noted that a greater number of citizens are willing to
participate in the anti-crime campaign, to do their part in
stopping crime.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the province's citizens provided
over 12,000 clues to police and helped arrest 722 criminals during
the May-September period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
