<HEADLINE> East China Cracks Down on Pornography </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
is set to launch a campaign against pornographic literature and
illegal publications.
</P>
<P>
According to an official, attention will be placed on
investigation and prosecution of major cases, a move that is meant
to crack down on the trade in pornographic and illegal
publications across the province.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the province is scheduled to come down
hard on both illegal and pirated publications, and that criminal
groups involved in making or dealing in those publications are the
campaign's major target.
</P>
<P>
He said that the province plans to impose severe penalties on
people in law-enforcement who violate the law and those who
falsify government documents, and that related departments have
decided to improve controls of the cultural market and to make
more regulations in this regard in the near future.  
</P>
</TEXT>
