<HEADLINE> Textile City Attracts 800 Million US Dollar in Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Basf Huayuan Nylon Company, a
joint venture between Huayuan of China and Basf of Germany, has
been established in a textile industry city in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture involves an investment of 180 million US
dollars, increasing foreign investment in the textile city to some
800 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The textile city was funded by Huayuan Group, a joint venture
between China National Textile Council, the Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation, and the Bank of Communications, in
Qingpu County of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Since it was established in 1992, the group company has merged
ten enterprises along the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The fixed assets of Huayuan is expected to reach six billion
yuan by the end of this year, and its imports and exports volume
will surpass 300 million US dollars. 
</P>
