<HEADLINE> Indian Finance Minister Optimistic About Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Indian Finance Minister P.
Chidambaram has expressed optimism over the performance of the
economy despite the recent continued slowdown in economic growth,
the Times of India said today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a meeting of businessmen here Monday, the minister
said the overall performance of the Indian economy this year (from
April 1996 to March 1997) will be as good as in 1995-96, with a
lower average rate of inflation.
</P>
<P>
Indian economy posted a 6.6 percent growth in the 1995-96
fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
He said industrial investment will experience a "marked upturn"
by the end of the fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Combined with improved performance in agriculture and steady
growth in the services sector, the fundamentals of the economy
will remain strong, he said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the recent slowdown in economic growth, the
minister said the performance of the economy in the first half of
the fiscal year should not be taken as benchmark as elections and
political uncertainty during the period had led industry to
postpone investment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
