<HEADLINE> China, US Telecom Firm Launch Testing Center for Optical Fiber </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The US-based Lucent
Technologies, one of the world's largest telecommunications
suppliers, has established a testing center for fiber-optics and
cables in Beijing through close cooperation with a prestigious
Chinese university.
</P>
<P>
According to "People's Posts and Telecommunications News,"
Lucent Technologies Optical Cable (Beijing) Ltd. spent seven
million US dollars on the center, and the Beijing Posts and
Telecommunications University will offer technical support.
</P>
<P>
Equipped with the latest examination facilities, the center can
test the special property of any optical fiber and measure nearly
all of the optical indexes.
</P>
<P>
The center will help the university accelerate the
commercialization of its research achievements in the field of
optical telecommunications, and will provide a good educational
service to the faculty and students there, the paper
reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
