<HEADLINE> Nepal Imports Tibetan Sheep and Goats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Tibet Autonomous Region in
southwest China has exported more than 5,000 sheep and goats to
neighboring Nepal this year.
</P>
<P>
With an average weight of about 30 kilograms, all the sheep and
goats, were provided by the Xigaze Prefecture in the southwest
part of the region.
</P>
<P>
The once-a-year export was completed within two months, and the
sheep traveled 860 kilometers before crossing the border.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities said that during the past 13 years, the
Xigaze Prefecture has exported more than 73,000 sheep and goats to
Nepal, earning foreign exchange of 1.42 million US dollars.
</P>
