<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Reservoir Area Grows Attractive to Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The investment environment in
the 60,000 square kilometers in the Three Gorges reservoir area,
from Yichang to Chongqing, is growing increasingly attractive to
overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
The central government has listed 17 counties and cities in the
reservoir area as open economic zones, and has granted much
preferential treatment to overseas businessmen.
</P>
<P>
To ensure the smooth progress of resettlement of around 1.2
million people and accelerate economic development of the
underdeveloped reservoir area in central-west China, the State
Council will soon implement a series of favorable policies to
encourage overseas businessmen to invest in the area, said Qi Lin,
director of the Resettlement Bureau under the Three Gorges Project
Construction Commission.
</P>
<P>
The country has intensified infrastructure construction in the
reservoir area since the world's largest water-control project
started in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The Yichang Three Gorges Airport was completed in October, and
Wuhan-Yichang expressway has opened to traffic. The country also
prepares to expand Jiangbei Airport in Chongqing and build Wuqiao
Airport in Wanxian, and plans to build Yichang-Guangzhou and
Wanxian-Daxian railways.
</P>
<P>
Apart from transport facilities, telecommunications facilities
have also been upgraded. International phone services have been
provided, and new telecommunications network is being built in the
area.
</P>
<P>
At present, China is building a group of hydro-electrical and
thermal power plants to provide adequate power supplies to
industrial development and daily life of 16.6 million people in
the reservoir area.
</P>
<P>
In Yichang and Wanxian, customs offices have been established,
and technological development zones at provincial or city levels,
which have a whole set of facilities, have been set up. Yichang,
the construction site of the project, even has bonded warehouses.
</P>
<P>
In fact, Yichang, Wanxian and Fuling have worked out local
favorable policies for overseas investors, and various districts
in the area are also simplifying procedures of approving
overseas-funded projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
