<HEADLINE> East Chinese Company Becoming One Of Top 500 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The Three-Strain Pharmaceutical
Company in China's Shandong province has planned to become one of
the world's top 500 by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
Wu Siwei, the company's chairman, says that it expects to have
30 billion yuan (3.6 billion US dollars) in sales by 1997, and 90
billion yuan by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Three-Strain is one of the largest private enterprises in
China. It was established in 1994 and sales this year are expected
to reach eight billion yuan (960 million US dollars), four times
last year.
</P>
<P>
The company has 18 factories across China, with 1,800 branch
companies, employing more than 30,000 people. In 1995, it was
granted the right of doing import and export business, and is
expanding its business overseas.
</P>
<P>
A Hong Kong branch has been opened, and other overseas
branches, in New York for example, are in the preparatory stage.
</P>
</TEXT>
