<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebels Attack Police Post In Eastern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 24 (Xinhua)-- Sri Lanka's Tamil rebels today
attacked a police post in Eastern province, killing two policemen,
according to military sources here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that a group of Tamil rebels attacked the
police post at Kolani, about 10 km north of Ampara town, around
7:30 hours this morning. Two policemen were killed and one
injured during the fighting.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that government troops confronted Tamil
rebels at Velvettiturai in north Jaffna district Monday and killed
one rebel.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting against the Sri Lankan
government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east
of the island country since 1983.  
</P>
