<HEADLINE> Ancient Rice Remains Found in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 24 (Xinhua) -- An archaeologist in central
China's Henan Province recently discovered the remains of some
4,000-year-old rice at a reservoir construction site near the
Yellow River.
</P>
<P>
The local archaeologist found a 10-sq-cm bit of paper-thin
cooked rice remains on a piece of pottery.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the discovery will benefit the study of
agriculture, plant cultivation, and customs in that distant
age. 
