<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets Azerbaijani Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Rong
Yiren met here this morning with a delegation from the National
Assembly of Azerbaijan, led by its chairman Murtuz Aleskerov.
</P>
<P>
Rong said this is the first high-level exchange between the
parliaments of the two countries and Aleskerov's first visit to
China after he was elected chairman of the Azerbaijani National
Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Rong said the current visit is bound to help increase mutual
understanding and friendship, and promote Sino-Azerbaijani
friendly cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Since China and Azerbaijani forged diplomatic ties in 1992,
Rong noted, there have been a frequent, high-level exchange of
visits, which have laid a sound basis for the development of
mutually beneficial and friendly cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said he hoped that through joint efforts, bilateral
cooperation in politics, trade, science, technology and culture
can be further developed.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China holds that all countries, big or small, are
equal, and state-to-state relations should be handled on the basis
of the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-Existence.
</P>
<P>
Aleskerov said that his visit to China is aimed at promoting
exchanges between the two parliaments, and to acquaint himself
with China's legislation during the reform and opening drive, as
well as the growth of China's agriculture and the construction of
special economic zones.
</P>
<P>
He said he hoped that the constructive relations of cooperation
between the two countries and their parliaments can be further
enhanced.
</P>
<P>
Aleskerov also gave an account of the domestic situations in
Azerbaijan and its foreign policies.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated the adherence of Azerbaijani government to a "one
China" stance, taking Taiwan as an inalienable part of China.
</P>
<P>
Rong expressed his appreciations over this.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Aleskerov conveyed Azerbaijani President
Geidar Aliev's greetings to Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
Vice-President Rong.
</P>
<P>
Rong also asked Aleskerov to convey regards of Jiang and
himself to President Aliev. 
</P>
</TEXT>
