<HEADLINE> Central China Provinces Support Development of Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hubei and Hunan
provinces have made notable achievements in supporting the
development of the southwestern Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
So far, the provinces have poured a total of 26 million yuan of
capital into nearly 70 projects in the remote Himalayan region,
according to an official source.
</P>
<P>
In May of 1995, 119 cadres from the provinces were sent to
Tibet for short-term work. The officials, after going down to the
grassroots units in the rural and pastoral areas to learn people's
living conditions, have contributed a number ideas to the planning
of local economy.
</P>
<P>
Ten officials from the city of Jingsha, Hubei Province, have
completed over 20 study reports for the development of Qonggyai
County of Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Personnel from Shannan Prefecture of Tibet have also been sent
to Hubei and Hunan for short-term training. A chromium smeltery in
Shannan, which stopped production for poor economic efficiency
for two years, has resumed operation with the help of 14 Hunan
technicians. 
</P>
