<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest China Co. Uses Blast Furnace Gas To Generate Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Blast furnace gas, which is
usually regarded as harmful, is currently being used to generate
electricity in Guiyang, capital of southwest China's Guizhou
Province.
</P>
<P>
The Shuicheng Iron and Steel Company has invested 57.54 million
yuan (6.9 million US dollars) in building four 6,000-kw generating
units, burning blast furnace gas.
</P>
<P>
The units generated 130 million kwh of electricity in 1995,
worth 35 million yuan, saving 150,000 tons of coal.
</P>
<P>
Blast furnace gas is an industrial byproduct of smelting iron,
and is less volatile and has fewer harmful elements.
</P>
<P>
Shuicheng Iron and Steel Company discharged 200,000 cubic
meters of blast furnace gas daily in the past.
</P>
<P>
The company will continue to improve the technology to make
better use of blast furnace gas, and to reduce acid rain damage.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
