<HEADLINE> Tanzania's Tea Production Goes up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania's Tea
production picked up to some 25,000 tons in 1995 from 16,000
tons in 1990.
</P>
<P>
A local weekly Financial Times today quoted Tanzania Tea
Authority (TTA) sources as saying that increased production was
achieved by a joint venture arrangement between TTA and the
Commonwealth Development Corporation (CDC).
</P>
<P>
The sources said on Tuesday that TTA and CDC had managed the
East Usambara Tea Co. Ltd., Kibana Farm in Njombe and Dabaga Farm
in Iringa over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
They predicted that the future of tea production in Tanzania is
bright and the rehabilitation work of the farms will facilitate
an increase in production when new capacity levels in the farms
is in full swing.  
