<HEADLINE> Afreximbank To Help Zambia's Non-Traditional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The Africa Export and Import Bank
(Afreximbank) has appointed the Development Bank of Zambia (DBZ) as
its trade finance intermediary in Zambia to promote the country's
non-traditional exports.
</P>
<P>
While confirming the apointment, DBZ Managing Director Gershom
Mumba said here on Monday that this new development unveiled a bigger
opportunity for sourcing funds for non-traditional exporters in
Zambia.
</P>
<P>
As a promoter of development, DBZ will provide pre and post-export
finance to eligible exporters engaged in production of
non-traditional exports.
</P>
<P>
Non-traditional exports have gained a remarkable progress in
Zambia. Their earning of foreign exchange kept growing from 124
million U.S.Dollars in 1993 to 149 million U.S.Dollars in 1994 and 216
million U.S.Dollars in 1995. It is expected to reach 250 million U.S.
Dollars in 1996. 
</P>
