<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hebei Regulates Property Right Transfer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 24 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province has issued a new regulation to ensure the supervision of
property right transfer of fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
Cong Fukui, deputy governor of Hebei said that, since 1988, six
cities, including Baoding, have set up organizations for property
right transfers, with a total trade volume of 310 million yuan
(about 31.3 million US dollars) to October. The transfers have
been greatly conducive to the mobility of fixed assets of
state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
However, some problems occured in the process of property right
transfers due to the lack of regulations, such as the devaluation
of the fixed assets in the trade, and the irregular operation of
the property right trade organization.
</P>
<P>
The newly issued "Regulations on Fixed Assets of the
State-Owned Enterprises in Hebei" stipulate the function, medium,
process and obligation of the property right transfers. It
includes the establishment of a management system, and punishment
for illegal actions in property right transfers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
