<HEADLINE> Ugandan Troops on Alert Against Rebel Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 24 (Xinhua) --The Ugandan troops are in full
alert against possible Christmas raid by Allied Democratic Forces
rebels in the west, said a report reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Soldiers of the Uganda People's Defence Forces (UPDF) were
preparing yesterday for shelling, targeting at suspected rebel
hideout in Rwenzori Mountain.
</P>
<P>
A local defence unit soldier said that rebels in the mountain
have been re-organising to launch a last-chance attack on UPDF.
</P>
<P>
Residents in the mountain have been told to leave their home
to avoid possible casualties. Some people in the mountain had
fled to a nearby town of Kasese.
</P>
<P>
The Commander of the UPDF's Fourth Division, John Kazini, has
said at a news conference in the northern city of Gulu that his
troops are ready to meet Christmas attacks by rebels in norther
Uganda. Salim Saleh, the Presidential Special Advisor on Security
and Politics in the north, also warned possible abduction by
rebels in the north in Christmas holidays. 
</P>
