<HEADLINE> Illegal Arms Factory Discovered in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Police in the southern Nigerian
state of Abia has discovered an illegal arms factory located in
Aba City, the "Punch" reported today.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman Ye Utan said they have arrested a man named
Ezekiel Uzuaru, who is said to be a veteran armourer in the
second World War and the main brain behind the illegal factory.
</P>
<P>
The police discovered in the factory one double-barrel pistol,
one single-barrel revolver, 30 expended shot-gun cartridges,
eight single-barrel shot-guns without butts and a number of tools
and materials for fire arms manufacture, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Inter-State Anti-Robbery Patrol Team of Nigerian police
raided the area after a robbery involving currencies and
valuables worth of three million Naira (about 40,000 U.S.
Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The raid also led to the arrest of four armed robbers
operating in the area, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
