<HEADLINE> S.Leonean News Paper Publisher Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, December 24 (Xinhua)-- The Editor and Publisher of
the weekly Expo Times, Ibrahim Seega Shaw and Acting Editor
Charles Roberts are still in police custody.
</P>
<P>
Two men were detained one week earlier by security officials
for a story headlined, ''Another Coup d'Etat, 11 Arrested - 2
Russians Involved'' on December 18.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that a police corporal, Majorocca Saccoh is also
detained after documents and handwritten scripts seized by
investigat ors from the newspaper's office.
</P>
<P>
Police officials declined to say whether or when the two
journalists will be freed or charged.
</P>
<P>
''Some suspects have escaped or gone into hiding'' after the
paper carried the story, an investigator said.
</P>
<P>
Claims by the two journalists that they were being detained
under sub-human conditions in an overcrowded cell were denied by
police.
</P>
<P>
Although the government has, up to now, not confirmed whether
there was a second coup plot or not, the Expo Times named 11 people
including two Russians, who are helicoper engineers, as co-conspirators.
</P>
