<HEADLINE> Indo-Bangladesh Joint Group on Ganges Water Meets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The first meeting of the
Indo-Bangladesh Joint Committee, which will decide the modalities
for the joint monitoring of the Ganges water, opened in Dhaka
today, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The joint committee has been constituted as per provision of
the 30-year water accord between the two countries signed on
December 12, which ensures the even share of the Ganges water on
dry season.
</P>
<P>
It was learnt that the joint committee in its first round of
meetings will finalize the monitoring methodology and select the
team of monitors who are due to be posted at four points to
monitor the flow of the Ganges water.
</P>
<P>
Official sources said the joint monitoring is expected to begin
on January 1 next year which also marks the beginning of the
five-month long dry season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
