<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News Analysis: Where Does New Economic Growth Outlet Lie (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Having analyzed market situations, economists believe urban
housing construction has great potentials. The conclusion has been
acknowledged by leading officials of the State Council, China's
top governing body.
</P>
<P>
The central government of China has listed housing construction
as new economic growth outlet and attached great importance to the
sector.
</P>
<P>
Though current real estate sector is still in a sluggish state,
experts say that housing becoming new consumption hit is a natural
trend, as housing sector does not so easily cause social problems
like automobiles, and on the other hand, it can recover investment
quickly and form a healthy cycle. Additionally there should be no
worries for marketing as every resident earnestly hopes to have
his own house.
</P>
<P>
At present, per capita living space in the Chinese cities is
7.9 sq m, and households with living space below four sq m in the
country's cities and towns total more than four million, and
dangerous houses with a combined floor space of 30 million sq m
are still waiting for rebuilding.
</P>
<P>
Real estate sector, especially housing sector can recover
capital in great amount and promote national economic development
by the means of consumption.
</P>
<P>
According to current selling prices for commodity houses in
urban areas, a standard flat will at least retrieve 100,000 yuan
of investment.
</P>
<P>
Because of its impact on more than 50 industrial sectors, one
Chinese yuan investment in real estate can create an additional
3.34 yuan of output value in related sectors.
</P>
<P>
However, prospects in real estate sector do not seem
encouraging. According to earlier reports, unsold commodity houses
across the country reach 30 million sq m, causing a serious
stockpiling of tens of hundreds of billion yuan of the investment
in real estate.
</P>
<P>
The main reason behind this lies in the fact that prices for
the country's commodity houses are too high, driving away a large
number of potential house buyers, and that most enterprises and
institutions are still building or buying their own apartments and
in turn distribute them among their employees by charging low
rents, thus preventing more consumers from entering the housing
market.
</P>
<P>
To vitalize China's housing market and cultivate new economic
growth outlets, China has been implementing housing reform with
earnest efforts and relevant departments have worked out policies
to reduce prices of commodity houses and to offer low-interest
loans to house purchasers and builders.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate that with various effective measures, real
estate sector, which has remained sluggish for the past three
years and is still lacking of vitality, will pick up soon and
become once again a focus for domestic and overseas investors and
a growth outlet for China's economy.
</P>
<P>
The fact has testifies these experts' forecasting. In 1996,
China has experienced the fastest growth in real estate investment
except capital construction. The central government has arranged
10 billion yuan in loans for comfortable housing project alone.
</P>
<P>
Information from the Ministry of Construction shows that this
year, real estate indexes in Beijing, Shanghai, Shenzhen,
Guangzhou and Dalian are climbing up. Experts say that in 1997,
following the return of Hong Kong to the motherland, China's real
estate market will further recover and develop into China's new
consumption focus.
</P>
<P>
Though real estate sector eventually becoming China's
consumption hit still needs certain environment, signs show that
the sector has owned conditions for supporting a sustainable and
rapid development of China's economy. As long as favorable
policies are available, real estate will surely become a new
growth outlet for China's economic development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961224.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News Analysis: Where Does New Economic Growth Outlet Lie (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- China has successfully
maintained a comparatively high economic growth while keeping
price increases at the lowest level in the passing 1996.
</P>
<P>
However, China still lacks forerunning industries in its
economic operations. Efforts have been made to probe new economic
growth outlets.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the country has formed a production capacity of 30
million color TV sets, contrasting 20 million sets of market
demands; while the country's textile sector has a production
capacity of 41 million spindles, with the market demands only
standing at 20 million.
</P>
<P>
One third of the state key construction projects which are
expected to bring forth bucks of profits after they go into
operation are actually starting losing money upon operation.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics released by the Ministry of Internal Trade
show that among the country's 443 kinds of industrial consumer
goods, only first-class cigarettes fall short of supply, and 99.8
percent of the commodities are either having a balance between
demand and supply or facing a state of supply exceeding demand.
</P>
<P>
Different people have different opinions as for what products
will become China's new consumption hits or what industries will
become China's new economic growth outlets.
</P>
<P>
Several years ago, experts and government officials first
thought of personal computers and telephones, while others put
forward tourism programs among common people. The fancy thinking
was later fixed on automobiles.
</P>
<P>
According to the "Outline of the Ninth Five-Year-Plan
(1996-2000) for National Economic and Social Development and
Long-Term Goals for the Year of 2010", China will make auto sector
into a pillar industry for the country's national economy in the
upcoming 15 years.
</P>
<P>
Geng Zhaojie, chairman of the board of the No.1 Automobile
Company Group based in Changchun, capital of Jilin Province, said
that making auto sector into the country's pillar industry should
have the following features: car production dominating the auto
industry; private uses of motor vehicles dominating the
consumption structure; an independent industrial network and
leading auto producers forming a certain production scale.
</P>
<P>
Families each with its annual income exceeding 30,000 yuan (one
U.S. dollar equals to 8.3 Chinese yuan) -- internationally
recognized income level for cars to enter the family -- now total
four million in China, but the auto market, with auto prices
plunging into the bottom in 1996, still have been operating at a
low speed for three years running.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, problems including traffic congestion and
environmental pollution are making experts worry about who favors
cars entering more families.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961224.0218 </DOCNO>
