<HEADLINE> 3 Killed in Police Firing in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- At least three people were
killed and six others injured when police opened fire to disperse
a protesting crowd in India's Bihar state on Monday, the Press
Trust of India reported today.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place when hundreds of people assembled near
a police station in Motihari district of the eastern Indian state
in protest against the killing of a movie hall employee on
December 20.
</P>
<P>
The protesters later went on a rampage and pelted stones and
brickbats at the policemen who opened fire when the situation
became "uncontrollable," the report said.
</P>
<P>
Two persons were killed on the spot and another succumbed to
his bullet injuries at a local hospital late Monday night.
</P>
<P>
Six persons, including a couple of policemen, also suffered
injuries in the incident. 
