<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Secretary-General on Election of HK Deputies to Ninth National People's Congress (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The statistics show that Hong Kong had a population of 6.31
million in 1995 (all the urban residents). According to the
above-mentioned proportion, it should elect 29 deputies to the NPC
(currently 28).
</P>
<P>
Taking full consideration of its special status, the number of
deputies of the Hong Kong SAR to the NPC should increase to 36.
</P>
<P>
On the election method, Cao said, in the light of the specific
conditions in Hong Kong and through repeated studies, a proposal
was raised for a meeting of electing deputies to the Ninth NPC in
the Hong Kong SAR under the sponsorship of the NPC Standing
Committee to be established, which is composed of members of the
Selection Committee for choosing the first government of the Hong
Kong SAR who are of the Chinese citizens.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the election procedures, Cao said the election
meeting will select 11 members to form a presidium to preside over
the election meeting.
</P>
<P>
The election meeting will be responsible for formulating the
concrete election method. Those who are nominated by over 30
members of the election meeting will be candidates for the NPC
deputies.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the number of candidates will be
one-fifth to a half more than the number actually to be
elected. The election will be conducted by secret ballots, and
those who get the most votes will be elected.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the presidium will announce the outcome of the
election, which will subsequently be reported to the NPC Standing
Committee for qualification examination, Cao Zhi said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961224.0221 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Secretary-General on Election of HK Deputies to Ninth National People's Congress (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Cao Zhi, secretary-general of
the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee,
today made an explanation on the draft method for electing the
deputies to the Ninth NPC by the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
His report mainly centered on the number of Hong Kong deputies
to be elected to the Ninth NPC and the election method and
procedures at the 23rd Session of the Eighth NPC Standing
Committee today.
</P>
<P>
Cao said Hong Kong will return to the motherland on July 1,
1997, and the present Hong Kong deputies to the NPC were elected
by the Guangdong Provincial People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Upon its return to the motherland, he said, the deputies of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region to the NPC will be elected
by the Chinese citizens among the residents of the Hong Kong SAR
in accordance with the provisions of the Basic Law of the Hong
Kong SAR and the number of deputies and method for choosing them
defined by the NPC meeting to participate in the work of the
country's highest legislative organization.
</P>
<P>
Cao said the term of the Eighth NPC will expire in March 1998
while deputies to the Ninth NPC should be elected before the end
of January 1998.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he said, the Fifth Session of the Eighth National
People's Congress, which is scheduled to be convened in March
1997, should formulate the method for electing the Deputies by the
Hong Kong SAR to the Ninth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
On number of deputies elected to the Ninth NPC, Cao noted that
according to the Election Law, the number of deputies to the NPC
elected by the provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities
will be allocated based on the principle of each deputy in rural
areas representing four times the number the each urban deputy
represents. That is to say that every 220,000 urban residents will
choose one NPC deputy, whereas one rural deputy should be chosen
from every 880,000 rural residents, Cao said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
