<HEADLINE> Expressway Becoming Operational in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the
93-km-long Zhengzhou-Xuchang Expressway in Henan Province has been
completed and was commissioned on a trial base today.
</P>
<P>
The expressway is an important part of the section of the
Beijing-Zhuhai National Highway in this central Chinese province,
which is a key state project for a period of ten years, covering
two Five-Year plans periods (1991-2000).
</P>
<P>
The expressway has four lanes and has a designed auto speed of
120 km per hour. The entire project was built in two stages,
costing 1.47 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
In building the expressway, workers have constructed 379
culvert passages, 24 bridges and seven flyovers.
</P>
<P>
Construction will soon start on another 49-km-long
Xuchang-Luohe Expressway, a southern extension of the
Zhengzhou-Xuchang Expressway with an investment of 960 million
yuan. 
</P>
