<HEADLINE> China Develops First Annular Laser Device </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- China has developed its first
world level annular laser device, an important step in China's
laser technology development.
</P>
<P>
The device was developed by Professor Gao Bolong from the
Changsha-based National Defense Science and Technology University,
after more than 20 years of effort.
</P>
<P>
The annular laser device has passed state appraisal.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the annular laser device is an important mark for
measuring the development of a country's optics technology. Only a
few countries, including the United States and Germany,
have mastered the technology for making annular laser devices.
</P>
<P>
The university established its laser research department in the
early 1970s, and Gao has led annular laser device research since
then.
</P>
<P>
He has also supervised a number of students of post-graduate
and doctoral degrees for China's laser science in the past few
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
