said the president can be discharged from the hospital on either
Christmas day or the day after.
</P>
<P>
The country's stock market tumbled Sunday over the surprising
news of Ramos' operation. But traders said the market will rally
with the recovery of the president.
</P>
<P>
Stunned by the news, both businessmen and congressmen demanded
strongly that they should be informed of the state of the
president's health.
</P>
<P>
The 68-year-old Ramos, whose six-year term will end in 1998,
had been hospitalized for three days early this month for what his
doctors said "a systemic viral infection." 
</P>
