<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Law Committee Vice-Chairman on Draft Law on Stationing Troops in HK SAR (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wang said that the first clause of Article Seven of the draft
stipulates that the troops' facilities, such as aircraft and naval
vessels, materials, and military personnel on duty who have
certificates and documents issued by the garrison, as well as
vehicles, will be free from checks, search and detention by the
law-enforcers of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
He said that the first clause of Article 10 stipulates that the
Hong Kong SAR government shall provide necessary convenience to
the troops for the fulfillment of their duties, and guarantee the
legitimate rights and interests of the troops and military
personnel.
</P>
<P>
In order to clarify the relationship between the SAR government
and the troops, the Law Committee suggested the clause be revised
as follows: that the Hong Kong SAR government shall give support
to the troops to fulfil their obligations for defence purposes,
and guarantee the legitimate rights and interests of the troops
and military personnel, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Referring jurisdiction over criminal cases involving military
personnel, he said the Law Committee suggested adding a new clause
stipulating that the military judicial department and the court of
the Hong Kong SAR, as well as the relevant law-enforcement
departments, can hand such cases to their opposite side for
jurisdiction if they think it is more appropriate, and after they
reach a consensus through consultations.
</P>
<P>
The Law Committee also suggested that civil cases concerning
infringements upon rights by military personnel who are on duty,
be placed under the jurisdiction of the Supreme People's Court of
the People's Republic of China, he said.
</P>
<P>
Damage compensation resulting from infringement of rights
should be acted on in accordance with the law of the Hong Kong
SAR, he added.
</P>
<P>
He also outlined other opinions raised by the Law Committee for
revisions to the draft. 
</P>
</TEXT>
