<HEADLINE> Mitsubishi Invites Parts Makers in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- A 60-member delegation from
the Mitsubishi Electric Corporation of Japan is in Shanghai to
seek Chinese manufacturers for fittings and parts.
</P>
<P>
It is Mitsubishi's first such move in China and so far over 700
Chinese firms have shown an interest in the business opportunity.
</P>
<P>
The Japan-headquartered firm has asked potential Chinese
partners to manufacture over 300 items for electricity generation
and telecommunications equipment, electronic elements and
apparatus, and such household appliances as air-conditioners and
refrigerators.
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi has chosen Shanghai to initiate such business in
view of east China's sound industrial foundation, and the large
number of local enterprises with a remarkable quality, technology
and viability level, said Shinmura Takuji, executive director of
the company.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident of China's economy and are willing to
cooperate with Chinese enterprises in the long term," he added.
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi Electric Corporation began to export elevators and
escalators to China as early as the 1950s. Currently it has 12
solely-Mitsubishi-funded firms or joint ventures in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
