<HEADLINE> Algerian Terrorist Group Makes New Threat to France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Algeria's militant movement, the
Armed Islamic Group (GIA), today made a new threat to France,
demanding French pressure for the release of its imprisoned
members in Algeria, Agence France Presse reported.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to French President Jacques Chirac, the group
threatened to "destroy your country" at all costs and asked him to
pressure Algiers for the release of imprisoned GIA members, who
have been given death sentences.
</P>
<P>
In the letter signed by the GIA's new leader Antar Zouari, the
GIA said it has chosen the path of killings. "We will do what we
say. The events of the past several days have proved it. We are
expecting some news in a brief time."
</P>
<P>
"The events of the past several days" may refer to the bombing
at the Port Royal subway station in downtown Paris on December 3,
but it didn't claim responsibility for the attack, in which four
people were killed and about 90 others wounded.
</P>
<P>
"You will certainly have some news about this in the near
future," the letter said.
</P>
<P>
In the undated letter, the GIA asked Chirac to intervene for
the release of its colleagues, including its chief Abu-Adlan
Abdelhaq Layada, who is jailed in Algiers.
</P>
<P>
The GIA put forward three conditions for the stop of killings:
the release of Layada and a number of other GIA members, stopping
support for the Algerian government, and paying a "tribute" for
"saving the lives of your people," referring to the French
nationals living in Algeria.
</P>
<P>
The French Interior Ministry said it is studying the letter,
but refused to make further comment.
</P>
<P>
The GIA claimed responsibility for a wave of terrorist bombings
in France last summer and fall.
</P>
<P>
The new threat came one day after a car bomb attack in central
Algiers killed three people and injured 70.
</P>
<P>
It also coincided with the second anniversary of the hijacking
of an Air France airliner in Algiers by GIA members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
