<HEADLINE> Longest International Container Route on Interior River Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The longest international
container route on an interior river in China went into operation
today.
</P>
<P>
A cargo ship loaded with international containers destined for
Japan and Australia left Yichang Port in central China's Hubei
Province this afternoon. The containers will be transferred onto
ocean-going liners in Shanghai Port in five days.
</P>
<P>
Yichang is the location of the Three Gorges Dam project. The
government decided to set up a customs office there and open a
regular international container route between the inland port and
Shanghai this October.
</P>
<P>
The liner will leave Yichang on 5th and 20th of each month.
</P>
