<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Rule Trust Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- A new game rule on trusts was
submitted to China's top legislative body in Beijing today for
review. The aim is to outlaw chaotic trust markets and
irresponsible trustees in China.
</P>
<P>
The draft law, which is parallel to international standards, is
expected to standardize management of trusts, and safeguard the
rights of property or trust investors, Zhang Xuwu, Vice-Chairman
of Financial and Economic Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC), said in an address to the 23rd Plenum of NPC's
Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
China's economic reform has endeavored to breathe life into the
trust business, reinvigorating it from a standstill two decades
ago.
</P>
<P>
A total of 392 trust corporations account for capital of more
than 600 billion yuan (about 72.3 billion US dollars), taking up
one tenth of the whole country's capital funds, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
However, the vaguely defined function of trust businesses, low
ability of risk bearing, and lack of self restraint, have plunged
the promising field into a tailspin, Zhang added.
</P>
<P>
He believes the lack of a specific law governing trust
activities in China is a major curse to ineffective mechanism and
loose supervision.
</P>
<P>
Zhang also defined the basic line of the law draft:
</P>
<P>
-- restraining trustees and guaranteeing the value of the
property and money, accredited to trust corporations;
</P>
<P>
-- regulating existing trust businesses to specialized ones for
particular capital and property management, and playing a role of
medium and long-term financial management, but different from that
of banks;
</P>
<P>
-- and stablizing trust activities to reduce the impact on the
business from the state's macro-control policies.
</P>
<P>
Non-business trusts are also on the list of regulations along
with business trusts, backbone of the field.
</P>
<P>
Despite its current limited transactions, non-business trusts
are promising, with more well-off Chinese appearing in the near
future, Zhang said. Trust organizations might become choices of
the future for individuals.
</P>
<P>
Non-business trusts also provides an effective means to guard
China's overseas capital.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the trust business of capital, securities,
property and fixed assets, trust corporations in China are allowed
to do business in loans, investments, leasing, safe box,
guarantees, deputy and foreign exchange, according to the draft.
</P>
<P>
Every trust corporation is subject to higher-level examination
and approval to help avoid possible risks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
