<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-24 13:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Stages Maneuvers Against Chemical Warfare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Some 13 battalions of Iranian
mobilization forces staged the second defensive maneuvers
against chemical attacks in Qom, 156 kilometers south of Tehran,
an informed source said here today.
</P>
<P>
The military source said that the maneuvers were held Monday
in order to "strengthen civil defense and prepare the
mobilization forces against possible aggression." Eleven men's
battalions and two women's battalions took part in the war game.
</P>
<P>
The first defensive maneuvers in Iran were held on December
10 in Ahwaz, the provincial capital of the southwestern province
of Khuzestan.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of elite fighters from Iran's Islamic Revolutionary
Guards Corps (IRGC) carried out the maneuvers including defense
against chemical-biological attacks.
</P>
<P>
Defending against chemical warfare has become an integral
part of the military maneuvers in Iran since thousands of
Iranian soldiers were exposed to mustard and cyanide gases
during the Iran-Iraq war between 1980 and 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
