<HEADLINE> Abandoned Baby Found in Trash Can in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 24 (Xinhua) -- As all children who have a
family are waiting for the visit of Santa Claus this evening, a
new-born baby of male sex was found in the cold night of Monday in
a trash can in Rouen, northern France.
</P>
<P>
A man, who was taking a walk near his house in the historic
district of the city, heard the crying of a baby and opened the
cover of the trash can, in which the Oliver Twist was howling
aloud in a plastic bag.
</P>
<P>
Police soon found the mother of the abandoned little creature,
who was sleeping in her dormitory. Both mother and son were
hospitalized, reported local media. 
</P>
