<HEADLINE> Pak-China Trade Links to Be Further Improved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 24 (Xinhua) -- There exists a great
potential to expand two-way trade and economic relations between
China and Pakistan, a Chinese embassy official said today.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting in Rawalpindi with members of the Rawalpindi
Chamber of Commerce and Industry (RCCI), Chinese Trade and
Economic Counselor Fu Guangting said Pakistan can export various
goods and services to China, particularly construction materials,
textile products, sports goods, surgical items as well as
manufactured goods and non-traditional items.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Pakistan Zhang Chengli expressed his hope
on the occasion that the meeting would be fruitful for further
promoting the cordial economic and business relations between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
RCCI President Sheikh Muhammad Shabbir said that China is an
important trading partner of Pakistan and quite a number of goods
were traded between the two countries, which mainly included
textile goods, raw cotton and leather.
</P>
<P>
However, the balance of trade is in favor of China. Shabbir
hoped that the trade imbalance will be narrowed through joint
efforts by the governments and business sectors of the two
countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
