<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aircraft Crash Kills 22 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- An Indian air force aircraft
with 22 people on board crashed in India's Andhra Pradesh this
evening, an Indian defense ministry spokesman said here.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft which carried members of an air force band was on
a routine flight from Madras, Tamil Nadu to Hyderabad, Andhra
Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
According to police sources in Hyderabad, all the passengers
and the crew on board are feared killed and the bodies and
military equipment were strewn all around the crash site.
</P>
<P>
The disaster struck following the failure of one of the engines
of the aircraft which crashed into the fields bordering Nellore
and Prakasam districts of Andhra Pradesh, South India.
</P>
<P>
The captain of the plane reported the snag to Madras Air
Traffic Control (ATC) and immediately after that lost contact with
the ATC, Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Prakasam district authorities have dispatched a
search team to the crash site.  
</P>
</TEXT>
