<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jobless Rate Remains At 7.5 Percent in OECD Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Unemployment rate remained at an
average of 7.5 percent in 28 countries of the Organization for
Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD) in October, according
to official statistics published today.
</P>
<P>
In Europe, the internationally comparable standardized
unemployment rates dropped in October in Belgium to 9.6 percent,
Denmark to 5.6 percent, Ireland to 12 percent, Sweden to 9.9
percent, and Britain to 7.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment rates remained nearly unchanged in October in
Austria with 4.1 percent, Finland with 15 percent, France with
12.5 percent, Luxembourg with 3.2 percent, and Portugal with 7.1
percent. But the rates went up in Germany to 9.1 percent and Spain
to 22.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the United States, unemployment rate stayed at 5.2 percent,
while those in Canada, Japan and Australia rose to 10 percent, 3.4
percent and 8.8 percent respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
